HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 836
By Marsh
A RESOLUTION to join in the celebration of "National Vending
Day" in Tennessee on March 5, 2026.
WHEREAS, the vending and convenience services industry in Tennessee generates an
economic output of more than $847 million and nearly $245 million in wages; and
WHEREAS, the vending and convenience services industry has expanded in recent
decades to include traditional vending and micro markets, office coffee and pantry services,
manufacturing, and small-drop distribution; and
WHEREAS, the vending and convenience services industry uses cutting edge
technology to deliver innovative options to consumers; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee is proud of the small business owners in the State who own
convenience services companies; and
WHEREAS, the industry stands uniquely equipped to service food deserts and
underserved communities throughout the nation through its supply chain, commissary, and
unique "last-foot" distribution expertise; and
WHEREAS, the National Automatic Merchandising Association (NAMA) has designated
March 5, 2026, as "National Vending Day"; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we join with the National Automatic Merchandising Association in the
celebration of March 5, 2026, as "National Vending Day" in Tennessee for the contributions of
the vending and convenience services industry.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
